  "text": "There are 2 types of ERs: ERα and ERβ. ISO can bind to either ERα or ERβ; however, ISO appears to have a higher affinity for ERβ. [CITATION_1] The activation of ERs by ISO is selective, that means that in some tissues act like estrogen and in others, as anti-estrogens. [CITATION_2] Therefore, studies in postmenopausal women have shown that soy protein and ISO reduces serum TC and LDL-C, and increase HDL-C concentration.",
